}
```

Fast API.

---

# Interview Explanation

“Yes, reducing joins and aggregations is important for better API performance because joins and group operations increase database processing, memory usage, and query execution time. In production we optimize by using DTO projections, pagination, indexes, caching, precomputed summary tables, fetch joins for N+1 problems, and avoiding unnecessary SELECT * queries. For large datasets we also avoid expensive COUNT and aggregation queries during real-time API execution.”
